Adults rest with their wings nearly fully open when active, and with them closed when quiescent. They all have a fast darting flight, close to the ground, which is usually difficult to follow. All species are likely to be attracted to flowers, and some come to damp patches and faeces. Most species, at least in southern Africa , seem to hill-top (
Henning et al. 1997
), but I have not made systematic observations in Kenya .
